 Here is a simple JavaScript program that will generate the ASCII characters and their corresponding hexadecimal codes from 0 to 127:

```javascript
for(let i = 0; i <= 127; i++){
    console.log(`Character: ${String.fromCharCode(i)} - Hex Code: ${("0" + (i.toString(16))).slice(-2)}`);
}
```

This program uses the `String.fromCharCode()` method to convert each integer into its corresponding character and outputs it along with the hexadecimal code.

Please note that this script only goes up to 127 as ASCII codes 0-127 are already defined, but if you need to include the extended ASCII codes (128-255), you can modify the loop to range from 0 to 255.
